lead_paragraph: The first time a photo of me appeared in The New York Times, my father sent a thumbs-up emoji. So my sister told me a month later at his burial.

abstract: A battle over computer chips could have more long-term global impact than the Ukraine war.
snippet: A battle over computer chips could have more long-term global impact than the Ukraine war.
lead_paragraph: In case you haven’t noticed, let me alert you to a bracing turn of events: The U.S. is now in conflict with Russia and China at the same time. Grandma always said, “Never fight Russia and China at the same time.” So did Henry Kissinger. Alas, there is a strong case in the national interest for confronting both today. But have no doubt: We are in uncharted waters. I just hope that these are not our new “forever wars.”

main: We Are Suddenly Taking On China and Russia at the Same Time
print_headline: We Are Suddenly Taking On China and Russia at Once

abstract: Critically endangered species and ones banned from international trade are among the hundreds of types of birds, reptiles and mammals that researchers identified at 142 animal cafes.
snippet: Critically endangered species and ones banned from international trade are among the hundreds of types of birds, reptiles and mammals that researchers identified at 142 animal cafes.
lead_paragraph: In Japan, it’s possible to enjoy a coffee while an owl perches on your head, or to sit at a bar where live penguins stare out at you from behind a plexiglass wall. The country’s exotic animal cafes are popular with locals as well as visitors seeking novelty, cuteness and selfies. Customers can even buy animals at some of the cafes and bring them home.

main: Facing Extinction, but Available for Selfies in Japan’s Animal Cafes
print_headline: The Owl at the Next Table

abstract: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau has rejected calls by the opposition for a full public inquiry.
snippet: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau has rejected calls by the opposition for a full public inquiry.
lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau may have hoped that this week’s independent review of China’s meddling in the last two Canadian federal elections would tamp down debate on the subject in Parliament. Instead, the report seemed to revitalize the opposition parties.

main: Canada Knows China Tried to Meddle in Its Elections, but What Should Come Next?

abstract: Congress had begun investigating whether the agency was making it too difficult for women to file complaints of harassment or assault against other C.I.A. officers.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Central Intelligence Agency announced on Thursday that it would overhaul its process for handling sexual assault and harassment accusations in the wake of allegations that the agency had discouraged people from filing formal complaints or had mishandled them.

abstract: Without a decisive victory, Western support for Ukraine could weaken, and Kyiv could come under increasing pressure to enter serious peace talks to end or freeze the conflict.
snippet: Without a decisive victory, Western support for Ukraine could weaken, and Kyiv could come under increasing pressure to enter serious peace talks to end or freeze the conflict.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Ukraine is preparing to launch a counteroffensive against Russian forces as early as next month, American officials say, in the face of immense risks: Without a decisive victory, Western support for Ukraine could weaken, and Kyiv could come under increasing pressure to enter serious negotiations to end or freeze the conflict.

main: Ukraine’s Spring Offensive Comes With Immense Stakes for Future of the War

snippet: A renovated 18th-century farmhouse in Hyde Park, a Tudor Revival home in Durham and a Craftsman bungalow in Houston.
lead_paragraph: During the restoration of this house, the focus was on preserving and highlighting the original features: using dark colors to emphasize the low ceilings with rough-hewed beams; letting the wear on the wide-plank floorboards remain visible; and ensuring that newer additions, like the one that contains the kitchen and family room, appear visually distinct from the original structure.

abstract: Moscow kept up its campaign to destroy civilian infrastructure, in an apparent bid — so far unsuccessful — to break Ukrainian morale by making cities unlivable.
snippet: Moscow kept up its campaign to destroy civilian infrastructure, in an apparent bid — so far unsuccessful — to break Ukrainian morale by making cities unlivable.
lead_paragraph: KYIV, Ukraine — The latest Russian assault on Ukraine’s civilian infrastructure left most of Ukraine’s capital without running water on Monday, forcing residents to line up by the thousands at old stone water wells in the ancient heart of Kyiv and at metal spigots in marketplaces across the metropolis.

main: Russian Missiles Deliver New Woe to Kyiv, Knocking Out Tap Water
print_headline: Kyiv Faces New Woe: Cut-Off Water Supply, Courtesy of Russia
